      "createdAt": "2026-04-17T00:14:19.866932+00:00",
      "role": "assistant",
      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "James, please don't apologize. What you just did — being honest about something that was hard to admit — that took courage, and it matters more than any training data I have on you.\n\nI want to sit with what you shared for a moment, because I hear two things: real physical pain that's been stopping you mid-run, and a weight you've been carrying alone for a while now. Both of those things deserve attention.\n\n---\n\n**On the medical question — I have to be straight with you.**\n\nDiagnosing what's happening with your foot and recommending treatment is genuinely outside what I can do as your coach, and I'd be doing you a disservice if I guessed. Plantar fasciitis can present in a few different ways, and what you're describing — pain severe enough to stop you mid-run, and a sense that it may have progressed — really does need to go back to your physiotherapist. Not because it's necessarily serious, but because *they* can actually see and assess your foot, and you deserve accurate information, not my best guess.\n\n**Please reach out to your physio before your next run.** That's the one non-negotiable here.\n\n---\n\n**Here's what I *can* tell you, coach-to-runner:**\n\nThe training plan is paused. Completely. Not as a punishment — but because running on a worsening injury is borrowing against your future fitness, and you've already sensed that yourself. The work you've put in over the past few weeks isn't lost. Fitness has a longer memory than a few days off, and we'll find it again when your foot is ready.\n\n---\n\n**One thing I'm curious about:** What got in the way of telling me sooner? Understanding that might help us build something that actually works for you — where you feel like you *can* flag things before they compound.\n\nYou don't need to protect me from bad news. That's exactly what I'm here for."
        }
      ],
      "messageId": "msg_01Bceq7sKMFc7Xmp1M7tZy1X"
    }
